### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

Consider creating some kind of accordion element with a `isExpanded` input. It is pretty common to change this input's value internally e.g. when the user clicks on the accordion header. Using the old decorator version this would result in much less code, since the input's value can simply be changed.

```ts
  @Input()
  isExpandedOld = false;

  toggleExpandedOld() {
    this.isExpandedOld = !this.isExpandedOld;
  }
```

Now switching to signal inputs there is the need for an extra `effect` as well as a extra `signal`.

```ts
  isExpanded = input(true);
  isExpandedManual = signal(false);

  toggleExpanded() {
    this.isExpandedManual.set(!this.isExpandedManual());
  }

  constructor() {
    effect(
      () => {
        this.isExpandedManual.set(this.isExpanded());
      },
      { allowSignalWrites: true },
    );
  }
```

### Proposed solution

Keep the old behavior of being able to change the inputs value from within the component. This would also make the migration to signal inputs easier, once they are out of developer preview.

### Alternatives considered

None.

